            <div class="post">
                <div class="post-header">
                    <span class="post-heading-text">ZHOU Xun</span>
                    <span class="post-heading-time">1991-2000</span>
                </div>
                <p>
                    In 1991, director Xie Tieli sought her out while she was still at school and invited her to Beijing to make the film "Tomb Raiden," after which Zhou went back to school to continue her studies.Zhou xun moved to Beijing in 1993 after graduation.
                    <br>
                    1996, and Cao Li starred in the comedy "Little Wives", in the film smart and clever Yangyang.
                    <br>
                    In 1997, she played the role of drug addict Shen Pei in the TV drama Red Prescription, which was adapted from Bi Shumin's novel of the same name.
                    <br>
                    In 1998, he appeared in the feature film "Glory of Flower Bridge".In the same year, he played a blind girl in the period drama Film Jing Ke and the Thorn in The King directed by Chen Kaige.
                    <br>
                    In 1999, he signed a contract with Beijing Rongxinda Film and Television Art Co., LTD.In January, the song September, sung by Pu Shu, was released, and Zhou Xun appeared in the music video of the song.In August, she premiered a drama series "The Red Lady in Green" starring Vivian Chao, in which she played the daughter of Fan Wenlan, a postal official in the Qing Dynasty.In the same year, appeared in the city life light comedy "happy is good", in the role of Tan Ge ge.
                    <br>
                    In January 2000, Zhou Xun played Lin Huiyin, a talented woman in the Republic of China.In March, she starred in a period drama "Ci of Daming Palace", in which Zhou xun played a young princess Taiping.In April, the song "Happiness", sung by Chen Ming, was released, with Zhou Xun as the leading actress in the music video of the song.In July, she starred in the taiping Heavenly Kingdom, a historical drama directed by Chen Jiarin, in which she played Shi Yiyang, the adopted daughter of shi Dakai, the "Wing King".In August, The Family of Fate premieres, starring Zhou Xun as Xu Hui's cousin Tao Tao;In September, zhou Xun won the best Actress award at the 15th Paris International Film Festival for her role as an active and mischievous girl named Peony in the movie Suzhou River, which was released in Hong Kong.In the same year, he starred in the drama film If There is No Love.
                </p>
                <hr />


                <div class="post-header">
                    <span class="post-heading-text">ZHOU Xun</span>
                    <span class="post-heading-time">2001-2010</span>
                </div>
                <p>
                    In 2001, "Like Fog, Like Rain, Like Wind" premiered, starring Zhou Xun as Du Xinyu, daughter of the Du family.She starred as prostitute Dong Dong in the modern drama A Hollywood Life in Hong Kong, for which she was nominated for best actress at the 39th Golden Horse Awards in Taiwan.
                    <br>
                    February 26, 2002, and Zhang Xinzhe co-starred in the love movie "Misty Rain Beauty" released, in the movie as a rich girl Zhao Anjing, Zhou Xun won the 25th Popular film Hundred Flowers Award for best actress;In May, zhou won the award for most Popular Actress among college students at the 10th Beijing College Student Film Festival for her role in the romantic drama "When Flowers Bloom", starring Xia Yu and Pu Shu.
                    <br>
                    In April 2003, Zhou xun released her first solo album summer, which included 10 songs.In the same year, li Yapeng and Wang Xuebing co-starred in the youth idol drama The Beach, in which he played a young single mother Ah Tong.
                    <br>
                    In January 2004, Zhou Xun won the best Newcomer award of the 10th Chinese Language List.In February, "Baby in Love" was released, in which zhou Xun played a persistent girl baby. For this film, Zhou Xun won the 2004 Actress of the Year award from China Film Directors Association.
                    <br>
                    In January 2006, Zhou Xun signed a contract with Huayi Brothers.In March, Zhou Xun won the all-around Artist Award at the 13th Oriental Storm Chart Awards ceremony.In September, starred in the ancient palace "the banquet", plays the prince waiting two youth female, and sang the movie's theme song "song, the more people", zhou xun also the film won the 26th China golden rooster best supporting actress nomination, the 12th Hong Kong film after award for best supporting actress award, the 26th Hong Kong film awards best supporting actress award.In 2007, he starred in the love suspense movie Mingming with Daniel Wu and Zhang Xinzhe. In the movie, he played the chivalrous heroine Mingming and the young girl Nana.
                    <br>
                    On June 30, 2008, the Chinese song "Rewind life" sung by Eason Chan was released. Zhou Xun co-starred with Eason Chan in the MV of this song.In August, she starred in the drama film Li Mi's Guess, in which she played the role of taxi driver Li Mi. For this film, Zhou Xun won the best Actress Award at the 27th Golden Rooster Award of Chinese Film, the Best Actress Award at the 16th Beijing University Student Film Festival, and the Best Actress Award at the 9th Chinese Film Media Awards.In September, zhou Xun was nominated for best Actress at the 28th Hong Kong Film Awards and best Actress at the 30th Hundred Flowers Film Awards for her role in the romantic drama Painted Skin, starring Chen Kun and Zhao Wei.In December, he starred in the romantic comedy Women aren't Bad with GUI Lunmei and Zhang Yuqi, playing ou Panpan, a female doctor with stuffy glasses.In 2009, she starred in the spy movie The Message, in which she played gu Xiaomeng, a specialist in the translation and television department. She was nominated for best Actress at the 46th Taiwan Golden Horse Film Awards and best Actress at the 10th Chinese Film Media Awards.
                    <br>
                    In August 2010, he ended his brokerage contract with his former employer Huayi Brothers.In November, his personal studio zhou Xun studio was formally established.
                </p>
                <hr />


                <div class="post-header">
                    <span class="post-heading-text">ZHOU Xun</span>
                    <span class="post-heading-time">2011-2021</span>
                </div>
                <p>
                    In 2011, zhou xun was nominated for best Actress at the 31st Hong Kong Film Awards and best Actress at the 31st Hundred Flowers Film Awards for her role in the martial arts film Flying Swords of Dragon Gate, which co-starred Jet Li and Chen Kun.
                    <br>
                    In January 2012, she starred in the romantic movie The Great Magician, in which she played the acrobatic family of Liu Yin. For this movie, Zhou Xun was nominated for best Actress at the 32nd Hong Kong Film Awards.In June, zhou xun was nominated by the China Film Directors Association for her role in the fantasy film Painted Skin II, starring Chen Kun and Zhao Wei.
                    <br>
                    On February 21, 2014, Zhou Xun was awarded the Chevalier de L 'Ordre des Lettres and arts;On October 27, she premiered the legendary period drama Red Sorghum, starring Zhu Yawen. In the drama, she plays Jiu 'er, who dares to love and hate and is not afraid to break through the feudal cage.With this drama, Zhou Xun won the best Actress of 2014 Chinese Drama Festival, the best Actress of the 17th Huading Award of China's Top 100 TV Dramas, the best Actress of the 2nd Hengdian Film and Television Wenrong Award, the best Actress of the 21st Shanghai TV Festival Magnolia Award and the nomination of the 30th Chinese TV Drama Flying Prize outstanding Actress.On November 28, zhou Xun was nominated for best Actress at the 34th Hong Kong Film Awards for her role in the romantic comedy "Sajiao Woman's Best Life", which she co-starred with Huang Xiaoming and Xie Yilin.
                    <br>
                    In August 2015, he was awarded the 17th Huading Award as the national Audience's Favorite movie star.
                    <br>
                    In July 2017, she starred in the artistic action film When will there be the Moon, which was officially released in mainland China. She played fang LAN, a thin, elegant, stubborn young girl.Zhou was nominated for best Actress at the 37th Hong Kong Film Awards, actress of the Year 2017 by the China Film Directors Association, and Best Actress at the 25th Beijing University Student Film Festival for her performance in the film.
                    <br>
                    On January 3, 2018, she won the 2017 Outstanding Actress Award of Film and TELEVISION Criticism Week of Chinese Academy of Arts;In August, ruyi, a period drama starring Wallace Huo, premiered, playing the lead character Ulanara Ruyi.In November, zhou xun was nominated for best Actress at the 55th Golden Horse Awards in Taiwan for her role as Yuan Zhihua in the drama film Hello, China, starring Qin Hao and singing the film's theme song, Look like.
                    <br>
                    February 12, 2021, with Chen Kun, William Chan co-starred in the fantasy film "The Order of The Gods" released, in the film as Bai Ni;March 5, with Chen Jianbin starring in the film "the eleventh time" released, in the film as the heroine Jin Ringling;On September 26, she starred in the period biographical drama "Exploits" directed by Zheng Xiaolong, as Tu Youyou, a pharmacist.
                </p>
